    "W. Nicholas Howley cofounded TransDigm through a 1993 leveraged buyout in which he acquired four struggling aerospace units from his employer, IMO Industries.",
    "The Cleveland-based aerospace parts manufacturer has grown into an $8 billion (sales) company through acquisitions of small companies that are the sole makers of particular components.",
